2026 Regular Session
HOUSE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 106
BY REPRESENTATIVE CHANCE HENRY
LAW ENFORCEMENT: Creates a Task Force on Utility Terrain Vehicles in collaboration
with Louisiana State Police and other appropriate stakeholders
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To create the Task Force on Utility Terrain Vehicles (UTVs) to study the feasibility of
3 implementing safety regulations regarding UTVs.
4 WHEREAS, some UTVs are capable of going upwards of sixty miles per hour; and
5 WHEREAS, UTVs can be made street legal and travel on public roads alongside
6 motor vehicles; and
7 WHEREAS, the UTV market rose above ten billion dollars in 2025; and
8 WHEREAS, the Consumer Federation of America reported seventy-eight UTV
9 fatalities in 2024.
10 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
11 establish and provide for the Task Force on Utility Terrain Vehicles to study laws and
12 regulations for the safe operation of utility terrain vehicles and to provide recommendations
13 or proposals for legislation. Any recommendations or proposals shall be submitted by
14 written report to the House Committee on Transportation, Highways and Public Works and
15 to the David R. Poynter Legislative Research Library as required by R.S. 24:771 and 772
16 before the convening of the Regular Session of 2027.
17 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall consist of the following
18 members:
19 (1) The superintendent of Louisiana State Police or his designee.
20 (2) The executive director of Louisiana Sheriffs' Association or his designee.
