9 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that at the first meeting, the members shall elect a
10 chairman and other officers as the task force may deem appropriate.
11 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall convene for its first meeting
12 no later than August 1, 2026, and once every two months thereafter.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a majority of the task force constitutes a quorum
14 for the transaction of business. All official actions of the task force requires the affirmative
15 vote of a majority of the members.
16 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the members of the task force shall serve
17 without compensation, except per diem or expenses reimbursement to which they may be
18 individually entitled as members of their constituent organizations.
19 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that meetings of the task force are subject to the
20 Open Meetings Law, R.S. 42:11 et seq., and records of the task force are subject to the
21 Public Records Law, R.S. 44:1 et seq.
